1180–1204","1204":"1204","1198":"1198","1240":"1240","1162":"1162","1180":"1180","England":"England, United Kingdom","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Lancaster","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Lancaster in northwestern England, which is recorded as <i>Loncastre</i> in 1086. The place takes its name from the river Lune + Old English <i>ceaster</i> ‘city, Roman fortification’ (from Latin <i>castra</i> ‘legionary camp’). The river name is probably British, perhaps related to Gaelic <i>slán</i> ‘healthy’, ‘salubrious’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Lawson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: patronymic ‘son of Lawrence’; see   Law   1. It is also found in Ireland since the 17th century.","Americanized form of Swedish   Larsson   and Danish, Norwegian or North German   Larsen  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Law","meanings":["Scottish and northern English: from a Middle English personal name <i>Law(e)</i>, a short form of   Lawrence  .","Scottish and northern English: topographic name for someone who lived near a hill, northern Middle English <i>law</i> (from Old English <i>hlāw</i>, which generally became <i>low</i> in the south and <i>law</i> in the north). Compare   Lowe   and   Lew  .","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 羅, based on its Cantonese pronunciation, see   Luo   1."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Fitzlawrence De Lancaster Lawson was born in 1162, in England, United Kingdom as the son of Lawrence de Lancaster Lawson. He had at least 1 son with Isabella. He died in 1240, in his hometown, at the age of 78."},"et":{"1162–1240":"1162–1240","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1198–1240":"1198–1240","1180–1204":"1180–1204","1204":"1204","1198":"1198","1240":"1240","1162":"1162","1180":"1180","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"1162–1240":"1162–1240","1162–Female":"1162–Kuollut","1198–1240":"1198–1240","1180–1204":"1180–1204","1204":"1204","1198":"1198","1240":"1240","1162":"1162","1180":"1180","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"fr":{"1162–1240":"1162–1240","1162–Female":"1162–Décédée","1198–1240":"1198–1240","1180–1204":"1180–1204","1204":"1204","1198":"1198","1240":"1240","1162":"1162","1180":"1180","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Fitzlawrence De Lancaster Lawson est né en 1162, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Lawrence de Lancaster Lawson. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Isabella. Il est décédé en 1240, dans sa